# The root user

Day one of an AWS account. You get **one identity for free** — and it's the most dangerous one you own.

## Unlimited & un-restrictable

Owns the account, has **full access**, and **no policy can take it away** — not even an SCP. Power you lock away, not use.

## Only root can

- Change account **email** / root password
- **Close** the account
- Restore admin access after a lockout
- A few **billing** + Marketplace seller tasks

## Root hygiene — non-negotiable

- **Hardware MFA** on; **never** issue root access keys
- Long, unique password, stored physically safe
- Then **leave it alone**
